video_title: Edegarike Kannada full movie 2013 HD
description: Edegarike (Kannada: ) is a 2012 Indian Kannada crime - drama film directed by Sumana Kittur. The script is based on Agni Shridhars novel with the same title name,which is based on his own experience. Agni Shridhar has written the script and dialogues for the film. Syed Aman Bachchan and M.S. Ravindra have produced the film under Megha Movies banner. Aditya, Atul Kulkarni and Akanksha are in the lead roles.[1] The film is based on the real-life incidents that occurred in the 1990s and is about cult figures in the Karnataka underworld like Sridhar, Muthappa Rai and Bachchan.[2][3]Directed by Sumana KitturProduced by Syed Aman BachchanM. S. RavindraWritten by Agni ShridharStarring AdityaAtul KulkarniAkankshaMusic by Deepak PanditCinematography B RakeshEditing by Anthony RubenStudio Megha MoviesRelease date(s) November 23, 2012Country IndiaLanguage KannadaProduction[edit]The two vital roles of this film - killer and to be killed - played by Atul Kulkarni and Aditya Singh is based on the script of well known writer and editor of Agni tabloid Agni Sridhar. Earlier, Bhavana was supposed to play the lead role. But she has been replaced by Aakanksha of Olave Mandaara fame. The reason for this sudden change was because Bhavana suddenly fell ill and the doctors advised her to not face the arc lights. While the director wanted to wait till she recovered, it was Bhavana who encouraged her to look for another heroine.[4] The film made its theatrical release on 23 November 2012.Cast[edit]AdityaAtul KulkarniAkankshaAchyuth KumarSharath LohitashwaSrujan LokeshDharmaMeghaResponse[edit]The movie received highly positive response both from the audience and from the critics. The critics lauded the movie for its stylish story telling, the performance of all the actors and theme of the movie. The times of India gave the movie 4 out of 5 and concluded saying This movie is for those who want to know the life of underworld dons. Gripping narration and excellent screenplay with a touch of romance make the story quite interesting. Except for a few gunshots, there is not much violence in the story that keeps you on the edge of your seat till the end. The director has woven a romantic track brilliantly which ultimately shows its strength in the climax. The DNAIndia rated the movie 3.5/5 by concluding that Take time off to watch the film, more so if you are tired of the same old formula films.The movie is said to have set new standards of film making in the Kannada Film Industry and has attained a cult-classic status. Agni Shridhar considers this movie as the one close to his heart.
